itten to disk before completing the task'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': 'I need to analyze this requirement. The user wants me to write a function that processes a string content by extracting certain parts based on their sizes, with specific examples and constraints provided. This is a programming task that involves:\n\n1. Understanding the pattern from examples (extracting words with even lengths)\n2. Implementing the function logic\n3. Saving to a specific file with proper formatting\n\nSince this is a straightforward coding task (XS complexity) and doesn\'t require the full software development process, I\'ll assign it directly to Alex, our Engineer. The task includes specific file requirements that need to be followed precisely.\n\n```json\n[\n    {\n        "command_name": "Plan.append_task",\n        "args": {\n            "task_id": "1",\n            "dependent_task_ids": [],\n            "instruction": "Write a Python function called \'parts_in_content\' that takes a string content and returns words with even lengths (as shown in examples). The function should be saved to \'/path/to/project/dir/something.py\' with only the function implementation and proper imports. Content contains only letters, 1-100 characters. Examples: \'This is a test\' -> \'is\', \'lets go for swimming\' -> \'go for\'.",\n            "assignee": "Alex",\n            "task_type": "coding"\n        }\n    },\n    {\n        "command_name": "TeamLeader.publish_team_message",\n        "args": {\n            "content": "Write a Python function called \'parts_in_content\' that processes a string content and returns words with even lengths. Save to \'/path/to/project/dir/something.py\' with only function implementation and imports. Examples: \'This is a test\' -> \'is\', \'lets go for swimming\' -> \'go for\'. Content constraints: 1-100 chars, letters only.",\n            "send_to": "Alex"\n        }\n    },\n    {\n        "command_name": "RoleZero.reply_to_human",\n        "args": {\